data.chText: （尤指因饥饿而）狼吞虎咽地吃光
data.enText: to eat all of sth quickly, especially because you are very hungry

data.chText: 津津有味地看；如饥似渴地读
data.enText: to read or look at sth with great interest and enthusiasm

data.chText: 无论是书、杂志，还是报纸，只要能弄得到，她都看得津津有味。
data.enText: She devoured everything she could lay her hands on: books, magazines and newspapers.
to be filled with a strong emotion that seems to control you

data.chText: 她心中充满嫉妒和憎恨。
data.enText: She was devoured by envy and hatred.

simple_means.memory_skill: de 向下 + vour〔= vor〕吃 → 吃下去 → 吞吃

means: (尤指因饥饿而)狼吞虎咽地吃光

ex.chText: 我通常吃燕麦粥当早饭。
ex.enText: I usually eat oatmeal for breakfast.
We took our time and ate slowly.

ex.chText: 那些香肠应该在两天内吃掉。
ex.enText: Those sausages should be eaten within two days.

synonyms.bx: 普通用词，通常指用餐、吃东西。

ex.chText: 他把早饭囫囵吞下，便上学去了。
ex.enText: He bolted down his breakfast and went to school.

ex.chText: 别那样狼吞虎咽地吃东西。
ex.enText: Don't bolt your food down like that.

synonyms.bx: 指匆匆吞咽食物，通常与 down 连用。

ex.enText: It is healthy to chew food well before you swallow it.
Babies like to chew on something when they're teething.

ex.chText: 男孩子们狼吞虎咽地吃光了汉堡和薯条。
ex.enText: The boys devoured their burgers and fries.

ex.chText: 我们坐在壁炉旁，大口大口地吃着牛肉和洋葱。
ex.enText: We sat by the fireplace, devouring beef and onions.

ex.chText: 我的狗每天至少要吃掉一罐狗粮。
ex.enText: My dog will devour at least one can of food per day.

ex.chText: 小男孩狼吞虎咽地吃下了半个苹果派。
ex.enText: The boy devoured half an apple pie.

synonyms.bx: 指饥饿时狼吞虎咽地吃东西，强调吃得快而彻底。

data.enText: to be filled with a strong emotion that seems to control you

data.chText: 她心中充满嫉妒和憎恨。
data.enText: She was devoured by envy and hatred.

example: Some people can down a pound of meat in the course of one meal

value.def: If a person or animal devours something, they eat it quickly and eagerly.

example.ex: A medium-sized dog will devour at least one can of food per day...
example.tran: 中型犬每天至少要吃掉一罐狗粮。

example.ex: She devoured half an apple pie.
example.tran: 她狼吞虎咽地吃下了半个苹果派。

value.def: If you devour a book or magazine, for example, you read it quickly and with great enthusiasm.

example.ex: She began devouring newspapers when she was only 12.
example.tran: 年仅 12 岁时，她就开始如饥似渴地阅读报纸。

value.tran: 如饥似渴地阅读;热切地看

partsOfSpeech.dec: carni〔= carn 肉〕+ vor 吃 + ous …的 → 食肉的
de 向下 + vour〔= vor〕吃 → 吃下去 → 吞吃
herbi〔= herb 草〕+ vor 吃 + ous 有…性质的，关于…的 → 食草的
insecti〔= insect 昆虫〕+ vor 吃 + ous 有…性质的，关于…的 → 吃昆虫的 → 食虫的
omni 全部 + vor 吃 + ous 有…性质的，关于…的 → 什么都吃的 → 杂食性的
vor 吃 + acious 多…的 → 吃多的 → 狼吞虎咽的
vor 吃 + acity 表状态 → 贪食
